quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  50,16,"It was We Who created the human being, and We know what suggestions their soul makes to them, for We are nearer to them than their jugular vein"
  50,17,"Imagine two guardian angels appointed to observe, one sitting on the right and one on the left"
  50,18,"Not a word do they utter, except that there is with him a ready observer"
  50,19,"And the shock at death will bring truth, “This was the thing which you were trying to escape.”"
  50,20,And the trumpet will be blown. That will be the day when warning will be given
  50,21,"And there will come forward every soul. With each will be an angel to drive, and an angel to bear witness"
  50,22,"It will be said, “You were heedless of this, now We have removed your veil, and sharp is your sight this day.”"
  50,23,"And his companion will say, “Here is his record ready with me.”"
  50,24,"“Throw into hell, every stubborn rejecter"
  50,25,"“Who made forbidden what was good, transgressed all bounds, cast doubts and suspicions"
  50,26,“And who established another god beside God. Throw him into a severe penalty.”
  50,27,"His companion will say, “Our Lord, I did not make him transgress, but he was himself far astray.”"
  50,28,"He will say, “Do not dispute with each other in My presence. I had already in advance sent warning"
  50,29,"“The word does not change before Me, and I do not the least injustice to My servants.”"
  50,30,"One day We will ask hell, “Are you filled to capacity?” It will say, “Are there any more?”"
  50,31,"And the garden will be brought near to the righteous, no more a thing distant"
  50,32,"This is what was promised to you. Everyone who turned in sincere repentance, and who are saved"
  50,33,"“Who had been conscious of God, the Merciful Benefactor, Unseen, and who brought a heart turned in devotion"
  50,34,"“Enter there in peace and security, this is a day of eternal life.”"
  50,35,"There will be for them all that they wish, and even more in Our presence"